	<region id="editorData">
		<node id="editorData">
			<attribute id="HowToTrigger" type="LSString" value="- Approach Jaheira's house from the front (near the bookmark)&#xD;&#xA;- Speak to the little girl infront of the entrance&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;Bookmark for the house: larian://bookmark?name=CTY_JaheirasHouse&amp;mod=GustavDev&amp;level=CTY_Main_A&amp;camPos=-198.180267;36.128036;-47.551403&amp;camTarget=-198.939575;35.720970;-47.043709" />
			<attribute id="needLayout" type="bool" value="False" />
			<attribute id="nextNodeId" type="uint32" value="29" />
			<attribute id="synopsis" type="LSString" value="Jaheira's youngest daughter is practicing with a sword outside the front door (Though she now runs in when she sees her, so this likely occurs after she's already seen Jaheira) she's demanding, inquisitive and insistent in a way you would imagine a younger Jaheira might have been. This conversation prompts when Jaheira returns for the first time, and I was aiming at this proposing &quot;Baldurs Gate always need saving and so few are capabler&quot; to play into Jaheira's personal dilemma" />
